HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language and is used to create the structure and content of a webpage.
HTML代表超文本标记语言，用于创建网页的结构和内容。

Most HTML elements contain opening and closing tags with raw text or other HTML tags between them.
大多数HTML元素都包含开始和结束标签，中间包含原始文本或其他HTML标签。

HTML elements can be nested inside other elements. The enclosed element is the child of the enclosing parent element.
HTML元素可以嵌套在其他元素内。 封闭元素是封闭父元素的子元素。

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Any visible content should be placed within the opening and closing <body> tags.
   任何可见的内容都应放在开始和结束<body>标记内。

2. Headings and sub-headings, <h1> to <h6> tags, are used to enlarge text.
   标题和子标题<h1>至<h6>标记用于放大文本。

3. <p>, <span> and <div> tags specify text or blocks.
   <p>，<span>和<div>标记指定文本或块。

4. The <em> and <strong> tags are used to emphasize text.
   <em>和<strong>标记用于强调文本。

5. Line breaks are created with the <br> tag.
   使用<br>标签创建换行符。

6. Ordered lists (<ol>) are numbered and unordered lists (<ul>) are bulleted.
   对有序列表（<ol>）进行了编号，而无序列表（<ul>）则带有项目符号。

7. Images (<img>) and videos (<video>) can be added by linking to an existing source.
   可以通过链接到现有源来添加图像（<img>）和视频（<video>）。
   
8. The alt attribute, which means alternative text, brings meaning to the images on our sites. 
   The alt attribute can be added to the image tag just like the src attribute. The value of alt should be a description of the image.
   If an image fails to load on a web page, a user can mouse over the area originally intended for the image and read a brief description of the image. 
   alt属性（表示替代文本）为我们网站上的图像带来了含义。 可以像src属性一样将alt属性添加到图片标签。 alt的值应该是图像的描述。
   如果图像无法在网页上加载，则用户可以将鼠标悬停在最初打算用于该图像的区域上，并阅读该图像的简要说明。

9. <!DOCTYPE html>, the declaration specifying the version of HTML for the browser.
   <！DOCTYPE html>，该声明指定浏览器的HTML版本。

10. The <html> tags that enclose all of your HTML code.
   包含所有HTML代码的<html>标记。

11. The <head> tag that contains the metadata of a webpage, such as its <title>.
    <head>标记，包含网页的元数据，例如<title>。

12. You can add a title to your web page by using the <title> element, inside of the head. A webpage’s title appears in a browser’s tab.
    您可以使用标题内的<title>元素向网页添加标题。网页标题显示在浏览器的标签中。

13. Anchor tags (<a>) are used to link to internal pages, external pages or content on the same page. You can create sections on a webpage and jump to them using <a> tags and adding ids to the elements you wish to jump to.
    锚标记（<a>）用于链接到内部页面，外部页面或同一页面上的内容。您可以在网页上创建部分，然后使用<a>标记跳转至这些部分，并向希望跳转的元素添加ID。

14. For a link to open in a new window, the target attribute in element <a> requires a value of _blank. 
    The target attribute can be added directly to the opening tag of the anchor element, just like the href attribute.
    为了在新窗口中打开链接，target属性要求值为_blank。就像href属性一样，可以将target属性直接添加到anchor元素的开始标记中。
    
15. Whitespace between HTML elements helps make code easier to read while not changing how elements appear in the browser. Indentation also helps make code easier to read. It makes parent-child relationships visible.
    HTML元素之间的空格有助于使代码更易于阅读，同时不更改元素在浏览器中的显示方式。缩进还有助于使代码更易于阅读。它使父子关系可见。
    
16. Comments are written in HTML using the following syntax: <!-- comment -->.
    注释使用以下语法以HTML编写：<！-注释->。

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
example:
code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <title>Brown Bears</title>
</head>

<body>
  <nav>
    <a href="./index.html">Brown Bear</a>
    <a href="./aboutme.html">About Me</a>
  </nav>
  <h1>The Brown Bear</h1>
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
      <li><a href="#habitat">Habitat</a></li>
      <li><a href="#media">Media</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
  <div id="introduction">
    <h2>About Brown Bears</h2>
    <p>The brown bear (<em>Ursus arctos</em>) is native to parts of northern Eurasia and North America. Its conservation status is currently <strong>Least Concern</strong>.<br /><br /> There are many subspecies within the brown bear species, including the
      Atlas bear and the Himalayan brown bear.</p>
    <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brown_bear" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
    <h3>Species</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Arctos</li>
      <li>Collarus</li>
      <li>Horribilis</li>
      <li>Nelsoni (extinct)</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p>Brown bears are not always completely brown. Some can be reddish or yellowish. They have very large, curved claws and huge paws. Male brown bears are often 30% larger than female brown bears. They can range from 5 feet to 9 feet from head to toe.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="habitat">
    <h2>Habitat</h2>
    <h3>Countries with Large Brown Bear Populations</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Russia</li>
      <li>United States</li>
      <li>Canada</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Countries with Small Brown Bear Populations</h3>
    <p>Some countries with smaller brown bear populations include Armenia, Belarus, Bulgaria, China, Finland, France, Greece, India, Japan, Nepal, Poland, Romania, Slovenia, Turkmenistan, and Uzbekistan.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="media">
    <h2>Media</h2>
    <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/codecademy-content/courses/web-101/web101-image_brownbear.jpg" />
    <video src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/codecademy-content/courses/freelance-1/unit-1/lesson-2/htmlcss1-vid_brown-bear.mp4" height="240" width="320" controls>Video not supported</video>
  </div>
</body>

</html>

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

end.
